# Educational books pipeline (school / college / trade)

**Goal:** Treat Textbooks and Education / Learning like instructional materials a district or school library would evaluate — not like novels.

## What boards & libraries look for (research summary)

US materials review (CA SBE adoption, TX IMRA/TEKS, local HQIM, ALA school-library selection) repeatedly asks:

1. **Standards / curriculum alignment** — covers the grade/subject sequence
2. **Factual accuracy** — no invented “facts,” careful claims
3. **Grade / age fit** — vocabulary and topics match the audience
4. **Instructional design** — teachable units, not story arcs
5. **Practice & checks** — exercises / formative assessment, not lecture-only
6. **Suitability** — appropriate for school/library use
7. **Clear organization & visuals** — diagrams/figures where concepts need them

We do **not** submit to state boards from this app. We **do** enforce these content pillars in our gate so books are built to that bar.

## Pipeline differences vs fiction

| Step | Fiction | Educational (Textbooks / Education / Learning / schoolbooks catalog) |
|------|---------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Cover first | Yes | Yes |
| Outline | Story Architect + beats/climax | Unit/lesson sequence + objectives |
| Editorial Brief | Blocking ≥ 6 (story) | Blocking ≥ 6 (**instructional** rubric) |
| Strict gate | Genre + dialogue + climax | Genre + **instructional materials** check (no climax) |
| Outline required at publish | Yes | Yes |
| Pedagogy scan | N/A | Cheap scan for objectives/examples/practice |

## Never

- Do **not** run climax checks on educational books
- Do **not** use popular-science / self-help author models for textbook craft
- Do **not** promote educational drafts on structural-only audits when content exists
- Do **not** build fixed two-column print replicas for digital schoolbooks (not required by digital HQIM / WCAG)

## Page layout

Digital school/library materials need **scannable instructional chrome**, not print manufacturing grids:
- Section callouts for Learning Objectives, Worked Example, Practice, Check for Understanding, Key Terms
- Diagrams inline with lesson text (`usesSchoolbookPageLayout`)
- Clear headings for accessibility (ADA Title II → WCAG 2.1 AA direction)

### Pagination formulas (do not reuse novel rules)

Fixed flipbook is **500×680**. Layout math lives in `shared/readerPageSplit.ts` (reader + storefront preview + quality gate must share it).

| Book type | Illustration rule | Fill rule |
|-----------|-------------------|-----------|
| **Novel / fiction** | URL art = own full page (Replit rule — still correct) | Half-empty page before art is OK |
| **Schoolbook / textbook** | Mid-size **inline** figures + teaching text on same page | Pack to **type-page depth** (~2–3 lines of slack at the foot — Chicago / trade practice). Densify thin leftovers; never orphan Example/Practice. Last chapter page may be short. |
| **Activity / workbook** | Same as schoolbook, slightly tighter line budget | Same densify + orphan rules |

Wrap at the **page edge** by estimated Libre Baskerville width — if estimate ≠ CSS, pages either clip (`overflow:hidden`) or look 25–75% empty. Recalculate `MAX_VISUAL_LINES` / `PX_PER_CHAR_*` against the real pad + running-title gap before changing art size.

